(json 63 (comment_id "749"))
(json 63 (user_id "771"))
(json 63 (proposal_id "6115"))
(json 63 (content "Hey everyone :)We are here to answer any questions or touch points you may have!In due time we will reply to all reviews, we really appreciate the excitement, support and criticism!"))
(json 63 (comment_votes "0"))
(json 63 (created_at "2024-06-10 11:12:33"))
(json 63 (updated_at "2024-06-10 11:12:33"))
(json 64 (comment_id "748"))
(json 64 (user_id "385"))
(json 64 (proposal_id "4734"))
(json 64 (content "Far more in the future, we will use some techniques to measure the effectiveness of this kind of video including:&nbsp; The numbers of event's hashtag relate to the video that we use in the event that that video support, or call to action... this kind of metric will measure the awareness level of the event, but also tell us how the video can help it.&nbsp; Engagement activeness of activities that relate to the video: not just viewing, not just sharing, we will also have some games and events relate to the video for our community members in the future to help spread the video. For example: the specific quest for that video, conversion rate from that video... so it will show the effectiveness of the video in very specific and practical way. Not just general like view or share or comment only.&nbsp; And more, but we will design more metrics base on the market at that time.&nbsp;"))
(json 64 (comment_votes "0"))
(json 64 (created_at "2024-06-10 10:53:59"))
(json 64 (updated_at "2024-06-10 10:53:59"))
(json 65 (comment_id "747"))
(json 65 (user_id "385"))
(json 65 (proposal_id "4734"))
(json 65 (content "In practical ways, as we got from some actual cases and one of that case is Catalyst working group storying telling video that was published, these are some key metrics that we based on to measure the effectiveness.&nbsp; &nbsp; I. <strong>Quantitative metrics:&nbsp;</strong> (1) <strong>Trend of video view and reaction</strong>: after publishing this type of video, even it have less views and reactions than other old videos in our channels, but its graph of view and reaction for this video showed that people love it more than others, and youtube also help to spread it faster than the other. It follow the practical algorism of Youtube that if there are first viewers love it, Youtube will help spread it.&nbsp; (2) <strong>Number of share on published video:</strong> this number in social media channels also more than others. Why? Because the audience love it. So, storying telling always be more attractive than others.&nbsp; (3) <strong>More comments in social:</strong> sure, this is the very practical way to measure the effectiveness. Through those comment we also get the insight of the audiences.&nbsp; &nbsp;II. <strong>Qualitative metrics:&nbsp;</strong> (1) <strong>Quality feedback from our partners before publishing</strong>: Yes, before publishing the video, we also send the script and demo video to some partners to check it to take the feedback then fix it. And the results is perfect, even most of them are love adn work on academy way. But they are all agree that our new approach of knowledge is really cool.&nbsp; (2) <strong>Quality feedback from audiences:</strong> this is the most important thing that every product need. So, we also have some good and bad feedback after publishing the video. But good reaction is way more than others also. That can tell us a lot.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;"))
(json 65 (comment_votes "0"))
(json 65 (created_at "2024-06-10 10:50:17"))
(json 65 (updated_at "2024-06-10 10:50:17"))
(json 66 (comment_id "746"))
(json 66 (user_id "385"))
(json 66 (proposal_id "4734"))
(json 66 (content "At first, it seems hard for an educational project to make attractive events to attract wide-range of target audiences.&nbsp;But! We're educational project that is using media in a very new way to attract wide-range of target audiences.&nbsp;
So, that is our key advantages compare to others to help us cooperate with many types of project in various fields including art, tech, content, entertainment... in a very practical ways. For example some case we will collborate soon in this time as you can follow our channel to join:

In this June, we will collborate and support ms. Ha - a Cardano ambassador - in materials production for the dRep course in Vietnam. We will help her to produce some graphic, video in our whiteboard style for helping the course participate easier and more engage. Besides, we will also collaborate with her channels and other related partners to that course to promote.&nbsp;
Further in July, we will join with an art project name NAVA Comic to organize an meme competition to wide-range of target audiences including comic artists global, developers or comic fan who love comic in general and fan of that comic... in that we will create materials for them, collaborate on making whiteboard video to help the audiences to know and understand about not just the event but also about the Cardano and other related tech to that project on Cardano.&nbsp;
Also with that NAVA project, we already collaborate with them to maka the first example of story telling video about Catalyst working group event on Cardano. And it had a great effects and feedbacks from the community. So, it's even can bring the idea of CWG spread easier than other kind of our old way.&nbsp;
And many more in the past, we collaborate with other projects on Cardano to make event to attract other target audiences that will be potential for our project and theirs.&nbsp;

So, it will be the same in SNET. We will open to collaborate with any project including academy and utility project. Our duties mostly will be transferring everything into more attractive and engage resources to attract the target audiences to the event or program of that collaboration.&nbsp;
After all, we our partners will receive better results than doing it alone, including the awareness, engagements, conversion rate... "))
