(json 73 (comment_id "739"))
(json 73 (user_id "734"))
(json 73 (proposal_id "6191"))
(json 73 (content "The use of NFTs as part of IPvX addresses allows not only to identify a node, but also to assign ownership to it, describing the ownership of the node to which it has been issued. The NFT can also contain certain unique characteristics of a node, allowing it to be used as a basic component in the Internet of Things. See our article [<a href=https://archive.org/details/ipv-x-ecosystem_202405/IPvX_Ecosystem.pdf rel=nofollow ugc>https://archive.org/details/ipv-x-ecosystem_202405/IPvX_Ecosystem.pdf</a>] and an earlier one here [<a href=https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/evolution-internet-addressing-from-dns-distributed-resolvers-ipvx/?trackingId=b1cxrzkxjw%2FsmQp38qZcXQ%3D%3D rel=nofollow ugc>https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/evolution-internet-addressing-from-dns-distributed-resolvers-ipvx/?trackingId=b1cxrzkxjw%2FsmQp38qZcXQ%3D%3D</a>].There is a section with examples."))
