(json 141 (comment_id "671"))
(json 141 (user_id "57"))
(json 141 (proposal_id "5295"))
(json 141 (content "Hello Gombilla! For sure it is a significant undertaking, but we feel confident we can do it, because we've already done the general DFA, learned a lot from that and this would be an opportunity to expand that to a community that has shown a lot of interest in Deep Funding, and that demonstrated how much easier it would be for them to learn and understand DFA if it was thought in their native language.&nbsp; So we have the chance here to combine our experience and knowledge with the huge opportunity in the Latam Community and the effort of the Singularity Latam Community that brought a lot of new people to participate in Deep Funding that need quality education. In addition, we agree with you, we clearly benefit and need partnerships, and we do have right now a partnership with Andamio for the educational project based learning platform, and a Partnership with the SNET Latam Community in the process of getting users to DFA Latam but also in the development of our content. In terms of sustainability, that is a huge concern for us we want DFA and DFA LATAM to be sustainable and keep improving in the long-run, and we have some solutions and ideas we are exploring for this but I don't and can't share anything that is not completely agreed and defined as we don't want to mislead people, but bottom line, we are working on sustainability and we have a few solutions to explore on that front so that we're not dependent on getting proposals funded in Deep Funding. However, we will still need to recur to the Funding Rounds for Expansions to new languages and specific territories and communities, because this expansion imply&nbsp; a lot of work. Setting up infrastructure, gathering a local team, creating tailored content, a lot of translations, and a strong marketing effort for the beggining where we start from 0.&nbsp; However, once they're established we just need to focus on sustainability for everyday operations and improvements."))
(json 141 (comment_votes "0"))
