(json 147 (comment_id "665"))
(json 147 (user_id "191"))
(json 147 (proposal_id "5028"))
(json 147 (content "Here is my mental model of this field: Regarding data, individuals/users will take care of the high quality data collection if they can become shareholders of the value created by it. The more of the analysis/model training can be done without data leaving the users&rsquo; control, the lower the price. Regarding algorithms, dynamically crowdsourcing, testing and combining different models so that there are always the best possible ones in action. Good incentives are crucial here as well. For the decision-making entity that creates the final service, user interfaces etc., it is important to have good governance for being able to respond to constant challenges. I&rsquo;d also give value to interoperability with other corresponding apps and data storage providers.
&nbsp;
&nbsp; &nbsp;It is definitely great that several independent teams with different strengths are working on the challenge, but what in your data, your algorithms or the user experience would make your application stand out from the other similar services?&nbsp;
&nbsp; &nbsp;If I think where the most likely potential in this service resides, I would say that it is some of your interoperable algorithms provided through the SNET marketplace and utilized by several independent service providers as a part of their backends. In either way, you are working on a highly valuable topic and I hope you will succeed."))
(json 147 (comment_votes "0"))
(json 147 (created_at "2024-06-08 16:29:16"))
(json 147 (updated_at "2024-06-08 16:29:16"))
(json 148 (comment_id "664"))
(json 148 (user_id "191"))
(json 148 (proposal_id "5686"))
(json 148 (content "I may be talking slightly past this proposal. Nevertheless, I&rsquo;ll share my short view of the future around this topic. Any time when one puts any information on the internet it will (have an opportunity to) include certain metadata that specifies the identity (or should I say agency) behind the contribution. Whenever the AI creates value that is based on a certain piece of training data, the agency behind that valuable action includes the identities who created that piece of training data. Surely there are tradeoffs in any design choices but in a grand scheme of things the AIs understanding of its own cognition and epistemology is not about morality but about intelligence. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;When we talk about data that is to be kept very strictly private, it won&rsquo;t be uploaded anywhere but stays locally in the owner&rsquo;s control. The technology of state proofs evolves rapidly. If I now think about this proposed service it sounds basically like a storage solution with optionality to grant different levels of access to different pieces of data (which is highly valuable in itself). But as stated, for many types of data the content is not allowed to leave the user&rsquo;s local storage. That is to be analyzed (and the value traded) by using private smart contracts or some corresponding emerging technology. My view is that the science and tooling here are in explosive progress right now. In this sense you are definitely working on the super crucial yet complex future topic. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Finally I just want to mention that what comes to privacy controls in general, my deepest hope is that this field would not follow the DeFi space with all the irresponsibilities, insecurities, hacks etc. If there is a single most important app domain for reviewed science, formal methods, strong audits and other such best practices, this is it. Good luck with the project, I hope it will become reality and succeed!"))
(json 148 (comment_votes "0"))
