(json 154 (content "Hi Gombila, thank you for your comment. I agree, and in fact online experiences, even web browsing, hasn't met the challenge of accommodating disabilities.
With my hundo x Ruby Room project I started to incorporate supports for visual and auditory disabilities, dyslexia, and perceptual sensitivities, as well as a start to provide for people with signficant mobility impairements. For this project I'd like to extend those services to include full blindness navigation. There is so much we can do to make online experiences work for everyone.&nbsp;
As you mention, access to high speed internet and game-ready computers is another barrier. With the Carbix MVSE metaverse, we relied on the pixel-streaming service Furioos to present high-quality immersive worlds to any browser.Furioos is no longer available, although similar services like Vagon do the same, at a price. In essense, using CDN high-speed servers and distributed processing can make this content more available to others."))
