(json 233 (comment_id "577"))
(json 233 (user_id "572"))
(json 233 (proposal_id "5116"))
(json 233 (content "Hey Gombilla,
Thank you so much for the positive feedback and clear input. This is exactly the kind of insight that helps us level up. Your point is crucial since it's at our core value propositions.
We&rsquo;re committed to transparency and consistency, which is why we&rsquo;re suggesting a methodology to deliver on this promise. As detailed in our proposal, deck (<a href=https://docsend.com/view/ht7ff9xignzaahv2 rel=nofollow ugc>https://docsend.com/view/ht7ff9xignzaahv2</a> )&nbsp; and video presentation (<a href=https://youtu.be/lxJ9qg4G200?si=WaKgyOoc7q3jxnVC&amp;t=1314 rel=nofollow ugc>https://youtu.be/lxJ9qg4G200?si=WaKgyOoc7q3jxnVC&amp;t=1314</a> ) , we plan to co-create criteria with community input and continuously use captured data points for improvement. This is not a static proposal/model; it will evolve and become even more relevant to SingularityNET over time.
Throughout the process, we aim for full transparency for all participants. Those submitting proposals will know how their submissions are evaluated, initiative designers will have an intuitive tool to communicate their strategic objectives to the ecosystem, and anyone wishing to get involved will find engaging ways to support projects in ways that bring the highest value to them and the individual project.
Transparency and consistency are key, and any suggestions to improve are always welcome. Thanks again for your comment."))
