(json 316 (content "This a daring approach and I would commend the proposer for thinking in this direction. However, One possible concern associated with the proposal for an SNET Conference &amp; Retreat Center in NY is the financial feasibility and long-term sustainability of the project. While the location in Plattsburgh, NY offers several advantages such as proximity to major airports, universities, and interstate highways, establishing and maintaining a retreat and conference center requires significant investment in infrastructure, staffing, and ongoing maintenance. Additionally, generating revenue from hosting AI/AGI/BGI events and retreats may not be guaranteed, especially considering the niche nature of these gatherings and the potential competition from other conference venues. I hope the team can factor in these considerations in their execution plans. Thanks"))
