(json 328 (comment_id "479"))
(json 328 (user_id "85"))
(json 328 (proposal_id "5570"))
(json 328 (content "hi Joey, thx for the questions:Link to projects completed, here you go:&nbsp;<a href=https://linktr.ee/edify_collabs rel=nofollow ugc>https://linktr.ee/edify_collabs</a> This should be in the prop - but may not have made being loaded up, so thanks for bringing it to our attention. :)Regards our DF3 prop - It is not anticipated that there will be any impact on delivery. AI-enabled Audit is a sizable project, but is running over 9 months with 4 orgs involved- with Edify mainly adding content and co-ordinating.This DF4 prop is part of the same roadmap, and will also be a partnership between four organisations. However, most of the heavy lifting on community build and management will undertaken up by Wada, who have teams in several African countries - and Cities, and have themselves run over 30 funded projects. FYI it is an MVP expansion of two 'proof of concept', Catalyst F8 projects we ran with Wada. So we are confident on delivery outcomes and timescales. Cheers Harry"))
(json 328 (comment_votes "0"))
(json 328 (created_at "2024-06-02 22:53:46"))
(json 328 (updated_at "2024-06-02 22:53:46"))
(json 329 (comment_id "478"))
(json 329 (user_id "711"))
(json 329 (proposal_id "5741"))
(json 329 (content "Thank you, Gombilla.&nbsp;You make some great points, and your concerns are valid and thought-provoking.
Part of the work in the ideation/discovery phase of the project includes identifying a tech stack that will allow for maximum agility in terms of deploying future ML integrations while simultaneously ensuring privacy and security of PHI/ HIPAA-compliance.
Mitigating components include data encryption, appropriate access controls, immutable audit trails, data segmentation and anonymization.&nbsp; Additionally, informed consent, employee training, Business Associate Agreements with third parties, and audit schedules are prerequisites.&nbsp; 
Quality and accuracy of ML algorithms with respect to personalized medicine in the field of mental health, will require time and experimentation to develop.&nbsp; Moreover, rigorous testing and ongoing QA efforts will be required to tease out biases in data collection and analysis to ensure positive, ethical use. &nbsp;
In consideration of the concerns you raise about the nascent intersection of ML and PHI, we strategically plan to build a SaaS-based architecture with future integrations and updates in mind. However, our initial focus will be on core PM functions to ensure ease-of-use and workflow automation for clinicians and administrative staff.
Initial testing will take place in our Portland-based clinic.&nbsp; Subsequent beta testing will include a small representative sample of our target market, followed by pilots with non-profits working in underserved areas with members of Medicaid &amp; Medicare.&nbsp; We will pursue strategic alliances with trade organizations and industry publications to create awareness."))
