(json 398 (comment_id "405"))
(json 398 (user_id "733"))
(json 398 (proposal_id "6215"))
(json 398 (content "These are great points and I will address them here.

50% is the milestone here for the first Ethics body. My working assumption is that after 1 year, there would be a progress review and we would elect new people or need to expand within 2 years. Ideally, it would be 100%, but I don't think that is achievable in the first iteration of the ethics body. Of course, those applying for the RFP can propose a higher accomplishment level.
You are correct that I do not have the expertise in ethics and safety.&nbsp; My expertise is:

Decentralized processes, including expertise in how to think about choosing and/or electing a stewardship or governing body.
Writing RFPs and specifications.



It would be better for SNET if we had ethics experts. We do not. In this Deep Funding round, I think there are only 2 or 3 proposals having anything to do with ethics and safety.&nbsp; The Supervisory Council (including myself) considers ethics and safety of primary importance. I wish someone else would have submittted anything that would give me confidence that we can address this, but nobody else did. Bringing in others is not bad (as your question implies). On the contrary, I will need to interview experts for this RFP, and when we post it as an RFP in the next DF round, it will draw ethics and safety experts into our community as they bid on this RFP. I do not expect to bid on the RFP (indeed, that would be a conflict of interest). This RFP is designed to be the first step in drawing in the right experts. "))
(json 398 (comment_votes "0"))
