(json 418 (comment_id "385"))
(json 418 (user_id "920"))
(json 418 (proposal_id "6215"))
(json 418 (content "Hello, and first thank you for sharing this thoughtful proposal. AI Ethics is a critical topic for all of us to understand and build better.
It seems elevating the ethics understanding of the organization is a good project, and I wonder why you chose to have only 50% of the organization beneficially trained? And what are the plans to enact this, is there an agreement with the organization, or can you make them, or is this just a statement in the proposal? I hope this question makes sense.
I'm also worried that you say that you also don't know enough about AI ethics and will hire someone. This person who will do the work seems like a critical component but there aren't any lists showing necessary qualification, expertise, or role needs listed for this person, and this doesn't seem well thought out. Is it perhaps possible to research AI ethics, and find a partner with exprience who can present to the community, so voters understand the future directions of the RFP with the person who will do the work.I would like SingularityNET to make sure they are training ethically everyone working in AI, and I hope you can elevate the proposal to demonstrate how it can be done in fact. Perhaps you could share in more clarity about what is actually lacking right now, what is needed for the gaps, and how you and an AI ethics expert might help to support.Thank you for all your time in answering, if you can."))
(json 418 (comment_votes "0"))
(json 418 (created_at "2024-05-30 05:49:42"))
