(json 440 (comment_id "360"))
(json 440 (user_id "596"))
(json 440 (proposal_id "5508"))
(json 440 (content "[Follow-up to the previous question] <strong>Q</strong>: Awesome thanks! And out of curiosity is this proposal focused on a specific kind of model or you believe your solution will be flexible enough to be used for all the models you're referred? <strong>A</strong>: The vast majority of benchmarks are Lp-bounded benchmarks, which work better with image, audio and tabular data. Text data is a bit trickier (because it needs to take tokenization into account), but there's currently research on extending Lp benchmarks to text."))
(json 440 (comment_votes "0"))
(json 440 (created_at "2024-05-27 10:46:46"))
(json 440 (updated_at "2024-05-27 10:46:46"))
(json 441 (comment_id "359"))
(json 441 (user_id "596"))
(json 441 (proposal_id "5508"))
(json 441 (content "<strong>Q</strong>: Is this [adversarial robustness] a problem that is faced by any AI model or is it more common with images? <strong>A</strong>: It actually happens with pretty much every AI model! Adversarial attacks have been found for image classifiers, LLMs, audio models, tabular data models&hellip; Most of the research/benchmarks are for image models because that's where they were first identified (and it's easier to study them mathematically), but some image model benchmarks can be extended to non-image models."))
(json 441 (comment_votes "0"))
(json 441 (created_at "2024-05-27 10:46:26"))
(json 441 (updated_at "2024-05-27 10:46:26"))
(json 442 (comment_id "358"))
(json 442 (user_id "259"))
(json 442 (proposal_id "6171"))
(json 442 (content "I would like to discuss with you privately.&nbsp;I've connected on linkedin and think we can have a proper chat about where to take this."))
(json 442 (comment_votes "0"))
(json 442 (created_at "2024-05-27 10:46:11"))
(json 442 (updated_at "2024-05-27 10:46:11"))
(json 443 (comment_id "357"))
(json 443 (user_id "596"))
(json 443 (proposal_id "5508"))
(json 443 (content "<strong>Q</strong>: Will SafeSuite be offered as an API? <strong>A</strong>: The benchmarks are run locally, but the Randomized Smoothing will be also offered as an API on the SNET Marketplace."))
(json 443 (comment_votes "0"))
(json 443 (created_at "2024-05-27 10:46:02"))
(json 443 (updated_at "2024-05-27 10:46:02"))
(json 444 (comment_id "356"))
(json 444 (user_id "596"))
(json 444 (proposal_id "5508"))
(json 444 (content "<strong>Q</strong>: Adv. Robustness methods generally require access to the models, how is this married with user provided (somewhat opaque) model hosting? <strong>A</strong>: Great question! Among the benchmarks, some are known to be blackbox benchmarks (which do not require access to models). Other benchmarks (i.e. whitebox benchmarks) theoretically need access to the model, but with some new breakthroughs (i.e. Neural Evolution Strategies for gradient estimation) it is possible to use them even without access to the gradients/weights."))
(json 444 (comment_votes "0"))
(json 444 (created_at "2024-05-27 10:45:42"))
(json 444 (updated_at "2024-05-27 10:45:42"))
(json 445 (comment_id "355"))
(json 445 (user_id "795"))
(json 445 (proposal_id "6171"))
(json 445 (content "<strong>1. Applications and Devices for EEG Sensors:</strong> Indeed, the evolution of wearable technology is a great example of how sensors can become part of everyday life. A decade ago, heart rate sensors were primarily used in clinical settings. Now, they are integrated into fitness trackers and smartwatches. Modern EEG devices are becoming more compact and user-friendly, embedded in headbands, helmets, and even earphones. These innovations make the technology more accessible. Potential everyday applications include <strong>Activity Trackers</strong> (monitoring brain activity), <strong>Productivity Assistants</strong> (enhancing focus and managing stress), and <strong>Mental Health Tools</strong> (offering insights into emotional states and cognitive functions). As the technology advances, its benefits will become more apparent, driving broader adoption.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>2. Data and Applications for General Health Questions:</strong> Your intuition is correct; the value of EEG data significantly increases when contextualized with the underlying activity or task. Our platform leverages <strong>machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI)</strong> to identify patterns associated with specific emotions and cognitive states. We provide <strong>Emotion and Cognitive State Analysis</strong>, <strong>Contextual Insights</strong> (optimizing routines for better concentration and positivity), and <strong>Personalized Recommendations</strong> (balancing dopamine responses, improving focus, and managing stress).&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>3. Advancements in Sensor Technology:</strong> You are right; sensor technology is advancing rapidly. Earlier EEG devices were bulky and uncomfortable. With advancements in electronics and material science, we now have <strong>compact BCI devices</strong> with soft electrodes, suitable for long-term wear. These advancements will help users track their mental states, identify stressors, and understand their cognitive patterns, building healthier habits and promoting deeper, more meaningful engagement.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>4. Project Timeline:</strong> We will update on this shortly."))
(json 445 (comment_votes "0"))
(json 445 (created_at "2024-05-27 10:45:27"))
(json 445 (updated_at "2024-05-27 10:45:27"))
(json 446 (comment_id "354"))
(json 446 (user_id "596"))
(json 446 (proposal_id "5508"))
(json 446 (content "Heya! I'm reporting here the Q&amp;A from the Spotlight Presentation in this thread."))
(json 446 (comment_votes "0"))
(json 446 (created_at "2024-05-27 10:44:45"))
(json 446 (updated_at "2024-05-27 10:44:45"))
(json 447 (comment_id "353"))
(json 447 (user_id "191"))
(json 447 (proposal_id "4657"))
(json 447 (content "You don&rsquo;t provide much information about how you're going to design the recommendation system. Do you have any preliminary architecture in mind? What do you mean when the AI service on the SNET platform takes inputs via conversational interface? It will obviously enable natural language explanation (as shown in the demo video) but does it introduce any inflexibilities? What if the agent that calls your service is another AI agent or one just has data in the spreadsheet? What if it is an automated control system of sensors with pictures and metadata? I just recently watched a <a href=https://magazine.mindplex.ai/introduction-to-solar-powered-farming-robots-highlights-from-s2ep11/ rel=nofollow ugc>video</a> of an interesting project that is about an automated farming rover able to carry a wide set of customizable sensors in it.&nbsp;I think for a recommendation system like this, it is important to utilize all the available information possible. If you are building the AI in-house, it shouldn&rsquo;t be any problem to do this.
<strong>&nbsp;</strong>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Secondly, in the final milestone you say &ldquo;seamless interaction and data flow between the platform and the AI services provided by SingularityNET&rdquo;. Are there already some services on the SNET marketplace you are going to integrate?&nbsp; &nbsp; Finally, any estimated timeline for the project?
<strong>&nbsp;</strong>
&nbsp;&nbsp;Empowering smallholder farmers is one of my favorite topics in blockchain/AI and I truly hope this project alongside all your partners in the ecosystem will succeed!
&nbsp;"))
(json 447 (comment_votes "0"))
(json 447 (created_at "2024-05-27 10:09:18"))
(json 447 (updated_at "2024-05-27 10:09:18"))
(json 448 (comment_id "352"))
(json 448 (user_id "191"))
(json 448 (proposal_id "6171"))
(json 448 (content "What applications and devices do you think will be the ones that bring crowds into wearing EEG sensors? I mean people don&rsquo;t use EEG devices as they use watches or rings. Maybe it will change in the future if there are applications attractive enough with benefits high enough from using them. I guess there are some semi handy ear devices currently(?) If we think about the person&rsquo;s general health questions, such as balanced dopamine responses that enable them to concentrate, work, study, stay patient and positive, what kind of data and applications are needed? I use a headband for guided meditation but it is very different from EEG when attending team sports or gaming. My intuition is that much of the value from EEG data materializes when the underlying activity or task is known. <strong>&nbsp;</strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Also, my understanding is that sensor tech is advancing rapidly so that in the near future we can expect much more accurate, reasonably-cost consumer devices. I don&rsquo;t know what I&rsquo;m trying to really ask. I&rsquo;m just trying to get some kind of understanding of what could be realistically expected from the coming years. People are losing their ability to do deep work, videos have to be shorter than 30 sec and they don&rsquo;t know why they are depressed. There is so much to win in this field by building incentives that overcome the habit of addictive shallow engagement and empower people. I really like this project and wish you a lot of success! <strong>&nbsp;</strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;And the final question: How long do you expect the project to take before the first version of the service would be on the SNET marketplace? Thanks!&nbsp;"))
