(json 454 (comment_id "345"))
(json 454 (user_id "240"))
(json 454 (proposal_id "5819"))
(json 454 (content "In terms of the market, in the initial phase, we will focus on emerging markets (countries that are developing, where access to high-quality healthcare is limited for many people, and where smartphones and internet usage are quite prevalent). Because these countries have a customer base with average income levels, they are increasingly interested in health and have a habit of searching for information about various diseases and their treatments online (Vietnam is an example)."))
(json 454 (comment_votes "0"))
(json 454 (created_at "2024-05-25 03:52:55"))
(json 454 (updated_at "2024-05-25 03:52:55"))
(json 455 (comment_id "344"))
(json 455 (user_id "240"))
(json 455 (proposal_id "6217"))
(json 455 (content "In this project, we focus on detecting anomalies in health monitoring data for elderly individuals. The goal is to identify dangerous issues such as strokes, falls, and other health-related emergencies. Initially, we concentrate on data collected through wearable devices. Furthermore, we collaborate with healthcare experts to explore additional data sources that can be collected (and should be collected) for specific health anomaly detection tasks. Thanks!"))
