(json 463 (created_at "2024-05-24 02:17:23"))
(json 463 (updated_at "2024-05-24 02:17:23"))
(json 464 (comment_id "335"))
(json 464 (user_id "652"))
(json 464 (proposal_id "5652"))
(json 464 (content "Dear Tommy, Thank you for your valuable feedback. As we've highlighted in the Las Flores overview, our Indie and <strong>Tech</strong> Film Festival is dedicated to promoting the understanding of emerging artificial intelligence technologies as tools for filmmaking and audiovisual projects. In line with our Marketing Plan, we propose organizing a workshop on AI applications in filmmaking to foster community engagement, attract new users, particularly young filmmakers and industry professionals interested in exploring the power of AI. This workshop will showcase real-world use cases of SingularityNET and complement our ongoing efforts to publish educational content on our social media channels. <strong>Alignment with Rule #1:</strong> This proposal aligns perfectly with Marketing Pool rule #1 by: <strong>Expanding the Deep Funding ecosystem:</strong> By educating and empowering filmmakers to leverage AI in their projects, we can encourage the development of innovative AI-powered filmmaking projects that align with SingularityNET's goals. <strong>Increasing community engagement:</strong> The workshop and ongoing educational content will attract and engage the AI and filmmaking communities, fostering a vibrant ecosystem around SingularityNET. <strong>Attracting new users:</strong> By targeting young filmmakers and industry professionals, we can expand the reach of SingularityNET and attract a new generation of potential users and contributors. <strong>Supporting ongoing community projects:</strong> The workshop and educational content will provide valuable resources and insights to existing community projects, further strengthening the Deep Funding ecosystem. We believe this initiative aligns seamlessly with SingularityNET's vision of a democratic and decentralized AI landscape and are confident that it will contribute significantly to the expansion of the Deep Funding ecosystem. Thank you, Andrea"))
(json 464 (comment_votes "0"))
(json 464 (created_at "2024-05-24 02:10:24"))
(json 464 (updated_at "2024-05-24 02:10:24"))
(json 465 (comment_id "334"))
(json 465 (user_id "532"))
(json 465 (proposal_id "5634"))
(json 465 (content "Thank you, Tommy. I did reply to you in one of your comments earlier on.&nbsp;
The questions are: where are the new users, where can one find them, and how can one find these new users? The honest reply would be that one would find them via their phones as they jump(scroll) from one social media to another.
And when one finds these new users what does one tell them? Another simple answer is to tell them about SNet and the existing wonderful solutions with the promise that SNeT is looking to welcome them as well.To be upfront, our team did think that this was fairly obvious as a concept. This brings us to your assertion saying most of which is handled within the Snet Ambassador program, there is a difference between social media posting and social media marketing, the difference is in the content, the duration of the campaign and the journey it takes the audience on.Our project seeks to make targeted posts based on carefully researched and listened-to conversations every day for 180 days at a minimum across six social media platforms. We know that the Ambassador program is not doing that.
As regards the KPIs across milestones, we have made necessary guarantees on our processes, which is where the guarantees should be. We guarantee what we will do, and we are careful to guarantee the numbers on platforms we do not have control over.
&nbsp;
Thank you Tommy.
Its been nice seeing your comments"))
