(json 488 (user_id "786"))
(json 488 (proposal_id "6104"))
(json 488 (content "Thank you for your thoughtful questions, HenriqC!
Regarding your first query about existing services for super-resolution, yes, there are other technologies available that enhance image quality. However, our service stands out because it is specifically tailored for medical diagnostics, ensuring compliance with healthcare standards and focusing on the nuances of medical imaging. Additionally, launching on the SNET web3 marketplace not only broadens accessibility but also integrates with blockchain for enhanced security and data integrity, which is crucial in healthcare applications.
For your second question, launching the ASR and super-resolution technologies as separate services on the marketplace is certainly an option. We considered this, but ultimately decided that a unified service would provide more seamless integration and user experience for healthcare providers. This holistic approach simplifies the workflow, reducing the need for multiple systems and ensuring that enhancements in image resolution and transcription accuracy directly complement each other. However, based on market feedback and needs, we remain open to the possibility of offering them independently in the future."))
