(json 496 (comment_id "303"))
(json 496 (user_id "191"))
(json 496 (proposal_id "6309"))
(json 496 (content "Great initiative! Identity management is of course a crucial factor in the SNET ecosystem as well. However, there should be a description of some clear way how the project helps SingularityNET decentralized AI platform to grow. <strong>&nbsp;</strong> The conditions on this Ideation pool says:&nbsp; &nbsp; &ldquo;The projects should align with the conditions and objectives of the New Projects pool, demonstrating a clear pathway to publishing or utilizing an AI service on the platform.&rdquo; &nbsp;"))
(json 496 (comment_votes "0"))
(json 496 (created_at "2024-05-20 11:11:36"))
(json 496 (updated_at "2024-05-20 11:11:36"))
(json 497 (comment_id "302"))
(json 497 (user_id "731"))
(json 497 (proposal_id "5842"))
(json 497 (content "Yes, of course&nbsp;it is compliant.&nbsp;The outcomes of this proposal will be:&nbsp;

<strong>Initial Knowledge Graph Deployment:&nbsp;</strong>A functional KG that represents all Deep Funding content, structured for scalability and future integration across the ecosystem.
<strong>Data Ingestion:</strong>&nbsp;Ability to ingest data from the main portal via an API offered by DF (must have) as well as other sources (nice to have) and to store it in the KG.&nbsp;
<strong>Thorough Documentation:</strong>&nbsp;provide comprehensive documentation detailing the structure and functionality of the KG to allow other teams to work with and to work on the KG.
<strong>Collaboration with Application projects</strong>: Coordinate with and integrate support for the teams awarded in the Data Applications RFP. This includes making the necessary APIs available for connecting data pipelines to the KG and searching the data in the KG.
<strong>Maintenance &amp; Hosting Plan:</strong>&nbsp;Accompany this with a maintenance plan to ensure ongoing support, hosting, and basic updates for 1 year (included in the maximum award).
<strong>Integration with SingularityNET's AI platform</strong> as a 'knowledge node': A minimum of 10% of the budget is suggested to be reserved for this purpose.
"))
(json 497 (comment_votes "0"))
(json 497 (created_at "2024-05-20 11:11:16"))
(json 497 (updated_at "2024-05-20 11:11:16"))
(json 498 (comment_id "301"))
(json 498 (user_id "191"))
(json 498 (proposal_id "6217"))
(json 498 (content "Is your focus on the service design for the elderly or on the anomaly detection AI ? Or equally on both? I think both are important but more challenges lay on the service design side. Old people are usually not that tech savvy. The devices and wearables they are able to use may be a bit limited which again impacts the data that they are able to generate. Yet another thing is of course people who are in the hospital/nursing home environments. Anyway, if you are able to come up with a service that is attractive to elderly people, it is a great step forward. As they face more health issues than the younger population, the system would be very beneficial to themselves as well as for the progress of science. I hope you can put together a comprehensive proposal for future funding rounds. &nbsp;"))
