(json 545 (comment_id "252"))
(json 545 (user_id "367"))
(json 545 (proposal_id "4917"))
(json 545 (content "<strong>Thank you Henriqc for your supportive words.</strong> We are committed to the growth and success of Citaldoc. We firmly believe in the transformative potential of AI and blockchain in healthcare and are excited about the opportunities these technologies bring to improve people's lives worldwide.
<strong>Integration of Blockchain Solutions</strong>At this stage of the project, we are progressing gradually, implementing payment for services with AGIX and ADA, offering discounts ranging from 25% to 80%. We plan to launch a Health Token, aimed at reducing costs for patients and serving as a savings mechanism for unexpected expenses. This aligns with the creation of a DAO in 2025 or 2026.
Blockchain technology offers us the opportunity to enhance the security, transparency, and control of health data. Practically, this could mean:- <strong>Crowdsourcing AI Algorithms</strong>: Encouraging collaboration among researchers and developers through blockchain-based rewards, fostering an open innovation ecosystem and contributing to our R&amp;D division.- <strong>Empowering Health Data Storage</strong>: Using blockchain to provide users with secure and transparent data storage options, allowing them to contribute their information for scientific research anonymously and consensually.
<strong>Current Data Usage</strong>As you observed, we currently use user data exclusively to formulate personalized prompts for precise and personalized recommendations. We do not store this data on our servers; it remains in the user's browser and can be deleted at any time. The future integration of blockchain, such as self-sovereign identity, will allow us to manage sensitive health information ethically and responsibly. These are future steps, but they are included in our project's roadmap.
<strong>Research and Development Division</strong>We envision this division as a think tank, a laboratory of ideas that influences decision-making and action formulation through evidence-based and rigorous analysis and recommendations. <strong>Our involvement with Cardano, SingularityNET, scientific medical societies, and other reference groups helps us find valuable human resources to add value to this think tank.</strong>
We will invite not only healthcare professionals but also experts in technology, artificial intelligence, blockchain, legal fields, scientific research, and other innovative profiles beneficial to the project.This group, meeting monthly and maintaining frequent contact, will focus on key areas such as:- <strong>AI Algorithms for Medical Recommendations</strong>: Developing and refining algorithms for more accurate medical recommendations.-&nbsp;<strong>Medical Research</strong>: Exploring new frontiers in medicine through AI, contributing to advancements in treatments and diagnostics.-<strong> Incorporation of Multidisciplinary Experts</strong>: Including specialists from various fields:&nbsp; - AI Experts: Bringing in expertise and the latest trends to evaluate their application on our platform.&nbsp; - Blockchain Experts: Expanding our understanding and utilization of this technology.&nbsp; - Scientific Researchers: Ensuring rigorous and detailed implementation of the scientific method in our processes.
<strong>Selection and Combination of AI Solutions</strong>To ensure we provide the best possible tools, we will implement a rigorous process of searching, comparing, measuring, and selecting AI solutions. This will include:- <strong>Continuous Evaluation</strong>: Constant monitoring and evaluation of available solutions, including those on the SingularityNET platform.-&nbsp;<strong>Collaboration with Developers</strong>: Working closely with AI developers to integrate the most advanced and effective solutions.
<strong>Services on the SingularityNET Platform</strong>We plan to <strong>launch multiple AI assistant services</strong> on the <strong>SingularityNET </strong>platform, adding to our <strong>existing services in medicine, nutrition, and psychology.</strong> In this stage, we aim to include services in <strong>veterinary medicine, physical training, and the much-needed text-to-speech</strong> feature, which will significantly impact the usability of our platform.
<strong>Future and Openness</strong>Currently, although we work with GNU software, Citaldoc is not yet an open-source or interoperable platform. However, in future updates, we will launch an API that will allow connection with other services, expanding the interaction horizons with other platforms. We recognize the valuable potential of human resources within the SingularityNET and Cardano communities and seek to integrate them organically into our growth.
&nbsp;<strong>Conclusion</strong>In conclusion, we already have active services on www.citaldoc.com, and new impactful services will be incorporated in this stage. We aim to have a multilingual and cost-effective platform with high usability. Once we achieve this stage, we can advance towards interoperability, linking the potential of blockchain with AI and applying it to healthcare, research, and education.
Thank you for your attention, and we apologize for the length of this message!We remain attentive to your comments and those who read this information.Jorge"))
