(json 554 (content "Hi guys,&nbsp; I find it super important that there are openly available AI based uncensored healthcare assistants universally accessible to everyone.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;What might your &ldquo;future of integration of other blockchain solutions&rdquo; mean in practice? Crowdsourcing AI algorithms and rewarding contributions? Or maybe blockchain empowered health data storage choices in a way that enables customers to utilize their data for scientific research ? As you are from Cardano circles you are probably aware that there is a lot of tooling under construction in this regard. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Currently the user data you are storing is for formulations of &ldquo;personalized prompts&rdquo; so that the customer can receive personalized accurate recommendations but the data is not used for other purposes, correct?&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;What kinds of things would the new R&amp;D division be doing? AI algorithms for better recommendations, or medical research perhaps? &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;How will you search, compare, measure, choose and combine different AI solutions so that you are always using the best possible tools at any given time? The hope is that there will be plenty of competing choices on the SingularityNET marketplace as well in the future. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;You list AI assistant services as something you are going to launch on the SNET platform. Is that one service or multiple services? Can other projects integrate them to be a part of their own corresponding health products/services and what would it require from them?&nbsp; <strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>I like what you have done so far and the fact there is already a service up and running. I truly hope this endeavor will grow and succeed!"))
