(json 557 (proposal_id "5440"))
(json 557 (content "Thank you for reading and giving your feedback on the idea.&nbsp;
First we understand the concept requires critical infrastructure, which is why we are proposing this as an ideation phase to deepen our research on the feasibility and viability of the project considering required technical tools and expertise. But our team is optimistic to create an astonishing solution to the problem we are solving.&nbsp;
Secondly, we intend to focus on the possibility of the project through this ideation phase to decide whether to make it open source tooling or a service on SingularityNET, however, some parts of our methods may not be fully open source most especially in the aspect of users data management and protection.
Thirdly, we have quite numbers of experts in each of the required fields to ensure the project execution comes to reality but only the information leaders of each of the will be added shortly.&nbsp;
Thank you&nbsp;"))
(json 557 (comment_votes "0"))
(json 557 (created_at "2024-05-17 10:40:32"))
(json 557 (updated_at "2024-05-17 10:40:32"))
(json 558 (comment_id "239"))
(json 558 (user_id "61"))
(json 558 (proposal_id "4503"))
(json 558 (content "Wow that's quite a lot of questions @<strong>HenriqC</strong> lol, but will do well to answer them accordingly.&nbsp;
First on <strong>market share gain</strong>, our approach to this is&nbsp;<strong>guerrilla strategy </strong>( bold creative thinking, more advanced technology, leveraging novel tactics, disruption and surprise and focusing on low-cost strategies to captivate the audience) and again the car rental ecosystem in Africa still lacks the technology to streamline process and enhance user experience which is what Drivepadi will be leveraging on and we're also building enterprise solutions for car rental companies to leverage our technology and we have some on our waitlist already.&nbsp;
On <strong>reputation system</strong>, all our users both renters and car owners will have a&nbsp;<strong>verification</strong> badge on their profile,users who have completed certain security checks using <strong>face recognition </strong>on SNET will then receive this badge to indicate their trustworthiness and is mandatory for all users, and also renters and car owners will be able to&nbsp;<strong>rate</strong> each other and leave <strong>feedback </strong>on<strong> </strong>on-time returns, vehicle condition, and user communication will contribute to a user's reputation score.
On<strong> predictive maintenance systems,&nbsp;</strong>yes this will work well by analyzing multiple factors, like  Brand, age, driven kilometers, and integration with car monitoring systems. <strong>maintenance History:</strong> Detailed records of past maintenance and repairs. <strong>user feedback:</strong> Incorporating user observations and feedback regarding vehicle performance. <strong>AI analysis:</strong> Using AI to predict when maintenance is likely needed based on patterns and anomalies in the data.
On <strong>Recommendation Systems,&nbsp;</strong>we will integrate existing AI services from the SingularityNET (SNET) platform that suits our platform needs and any unavailable tool will be recommended for custom development and deployment to the SingularityNET marketplace by our team (in the next round) or to the community.&nbsp;
Lastly on the <strong>project timeline,&nbsp;</strong>we have a 6month clear roadmap to develop, execute and implement this project as captured in the milestones.&nbsp;
Thanks"))
