(json 603 (user_id "30"))
(json 603 (proposal_id "4872"))
(json 603 (content "I have gone through your proposal, very ambitious and exciting proposal it is, I love the fact that it will be providing a database hosted onto the SingularityNet platform for humanoid data, which can then be used by anyone to train their robots. The decentralised platform approach will definitely give more realistic examples that can be used to train robots.
What I am rather concerned is that you propose to pay contributors with AGIX while going ahead to do a token launch. I read it that you truly want to pay contributors with the token and not AGIX which is not bad, but you just needed to be explicit about, otherwise the token can be read as not too necessary to the proposal if it's not directly helping the process&nbsp;"))
(json 603 (comment_votes "1"))
(json 603 (created_at "2024-05-11 05:29:05"))
(json 603 (updated_at "2024-05-11 05:29:05"))
(json 604 (comment_id "191"))
(json 604 (user_id "458"))
(json 604 (proposal_id "4831"))
(json 604 (content "Hello there, thank you very much for the post. Please, I have just updated my milestones now, there should be more clarity on the duration. I am Looking to complete development within 5months and commence testing and commercialisation there after.&nbsp; The project itself would take 12months at the most.&nbsp; Regarding the principles of SNET, I've read through the portal severally and I've been in the community for quite sometime and do have an understanding of Singularity Net as a wholeand its values and its about building a more just and more compassionate society through AI. The three core focus areas from my understanding are decentralisation, democracy and beneficial AGI and this project does align well with it. This project seeks to use AI in a way that makes everyday work tasks easier for humans by automating daily work routines and supporting decision making as well as for developing the security component in the application. I wouldn&rsquo;t be using AI except to enhance human life neither would I consider to use if it were not beneficial to humanity as a whole.&nbsp; The solution would support decentralisation through the use of blockchain technology harnessing blockchain technology alongside AI to provide optimal security for its users. To support democracy, I&rsquo;ve considered making it such that every decision is made by voting. Team members can propose ideas, and others can vote on them. The ideas with the most votes get implemented, fostering a democratic and collaborative work environment. Our first challenge with this would be that our solutions would be open to everyone and not all customers might want to to adopt that decision making model and all company&rsquo;s already have a decision making process in place and developing it this way may limit our propagation. I can however include this as an optional&nbsp; feature for our customers. I hope this addresses all your concerns, I'm happy to address any further queries. Thank you very much. &nbsp; &nbsp;"))
(json 604 (comment_votes "0"))
(json 604 (created_at "2024-05-09 15:04:05"))
(json 604 (updated_at "2024-05-09 15:04:05"))
(json 605 (comment_id "190"))
(json 605 (user_id "323"))
(json 605 (proposal_id "4528"))
(json 605 (content "Hi team,
It's an intriguing proposal to leverage the success that the Deep Funding has sponsored for projects to attract even more new projects. But I have a concern about what difficulties and challenges the implementation of this project might entail for our team while still ensuring successful outcomes?"))
(json 605 (comment_votes "0"))
(json 605 (created_at "2024-05-09 07:31:46"))
(json 605 (updated_at "2024-05-09 07:31:46"))
(json 606 (comment_id "189"))
(json 606 (user_id "61"))
(json 606 (proposal_id "4503"))
(json 606 (content "Hello,
Many thanks for the questions and concerns. Firstly, let me clarify what we are building is a car rental platform more like Airbnb for car rental or platform similar to <a href=https://turo.com/ rel=nofollow ugc>Turo.</a>
Secondly, Drivepadi is a B2B,B2C startup so the user mentioned in the proposal refers to both renters (individuals looking to rent cars) and hosts (car owners or car rental companies) using our platform. The proposal outlines the integration and implementation of Snet AI services within DrivePadi's platform. These services will analyze user data, enhanced security, user verification, including renter preferences and market trends, to provide personalized car rental experience. DrivePadi is a platform that facilitates both renting cars (for individuals) and renting cars out (for car owners or rental companies).&nbsp;&nbsp;
Lastly, the $100,000 funding is to develop, integrate, and optimize these AI-driven features of SingularityNET AI marketplace within DrivePadi's platform, ultimately improving user satisfaction, engagement, and business outcomes as detailed in our milestones.
Hope these addresses your concerns, if not please feel free to indicate areas you still need more clarifications.
Thanks."))
(json 606 (comment_votes "0"))
