(json 639 (comment_id "141"))
(json 639 (user_id "33"))
(json 639 (proposal_id "4516"))
(json 639 (content "Hi Ahan : first, a lot of the framework for processing is defined within Identus. Then, there is a requirement for a full Trust Registry, which is one of the main delivery of my Milestone 1.&nbsp; In regards to data privacy, i will refer you to how VCs are generally built via DIDComm (secure messaging between 2 unrelated parties), plus the fact that VCs are generally NOT onchain (to avoid the risk of encrypted data being broken in a few years when quantum algo get mainstream).&nbsp;
In addition, we are talking here about an AI's digital identity, so not a human data privacy issue per say.
Happy to give you a bit more info on the topic if necessary, but I think you start to get some answers to your question.
Kind regards - Eric"))
(json 639 (comment_votes "0"))
(json 639 (created_at "2024-05-02 11:24:34"))
(json 639 (updated_at "2024-05-02 11:24:34"))
(json 640 (comment_id "140"))
(json 640 (user_id "33"))
(json 640 (proposal_id "4516"))
(json 640 (content "Hi Ahan - the idea is that EACH transaction is marked in a Verifiable Credential (VC), and also each supplier of the AI gets a way to verify its supplier (of model, GPU, or even annother full AI acting as service provider), by checking its VCs. So if an AI starts to take more money than it should, or takes a longer time than advertised, or fails too often, etc... then this is immediately stamped for ever in a VC accessible to all those wanting to call this AI's service. The AI reputation is a live one, and can improve or get worse at each call. I am not going in further details here, but I think you can get the point.
Kind regards - Eric"))
(json 640 (comment_votes "0"))
(json 640 (created_at "2024-05-02 11:19:21"))
(json 640 (updated_at "2024-05-02 11:19:21"))
(json 641 (comment_id "139"))
(json 641 (user_id "33"))
(json 641 (proposal_id "4516"))
(json 641 (content "Hey Jan - thank you for your feedback here. As you know, I have been in the Atala Prism ecosystem for around 18 months now. Prior to this, I have developed 2 identity/authentication solutions (SignWithWallet.com and authenly.com).
In relation to DIDs and VCs, in the end, the current situation with Identus is thst those DIDs would be issued on the Cardano Blockchain, in what could be seen as a Digital Identity wallet (although to my view, it could/should also be used as a payment wallet).&nbsp;
I am happy to continue the discussion either here or in a separate channel.
Kind regards - Eric&nbsp;"))
(json 641 (comment_votes "0"))
(json 641 (created_at "2024-05-02 11:14:11"))
(json 641 (updated_at "2024-05-02 11:14:11"))
