(json 643 (proposal_id "4779"))
(json 643 (content "Hey! Yes, answering the second part, the plan is to open-source this completely, and should be available for usage by everyone. For usage of LLMs, we shall allocate credits for usage of open-source models, but for OpenAI models like GPT-4, for the open-source version, I'll create a placeholder for user to use their API token.&nbsp;
For the first part, Zenith.ai is a team of 4 currently, its still in a very nascent phase right now, but during the course of this project, you can expect that our team will be more public (Website, blog, linkedin presence) for better publicity. But it wouldn&rsquo;t hamper the open-source nature of this project in any manner. I'd see Zenith.ai just as banner for a charter of various AI based projects open to public for usage. Will need to be how our team can officially associate with singularity.net with this milestone. Does that answer your question?"))
