(json 666 (comment_id "113"))
(json 666 (user_id "18"))
(json 666 (proposal_id "4326"))
(json 666 (content "In the spirit of decentralization of power,&nbsp;there is an opportunity in the construction of this new process to implement and test a trias politica on a small scale, similar to what's suggested in&nbsp;<a href=https://singularitynet.io/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/SingComDao-Initiation-Document-170423.pdf rel=nofollow ugc>https://singularitynet.io/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/SingComDao-Initiation-Document-170423.pdf</a> in a larger context.
If 1) specification, 2) filtering / quality assurance, and 3) development of an RFP are separated, so could be the persons or groups that participate in these different roles. A good decoupling would mean that no agent, be it an individual or a team, has influence on more than one of these three aspects. The expected effect is that conflicting interests and&nbsp;perverse incentives are reduced, thereby lowering the chance of observing undesired side-effects, such as the formulation of self-serving RFPs (as mentioned in the article) or the bypassing of QA for RFPs that can be easily developed but don't hold up to some quality standard."))
(json 666 (comment_votes "1"))
